         <crm:E52_Time-span>
            <crm:P78_is_identified_by>He was an Egyptian martyr who was originally a Muslim and converted to Christianity marrying a Christian woman. 
                  Denounced as a convert to Christianity, he and his wife were imprisoned, tortured and exiled. 
                  He was again imprisoned by the governor of his locality but despite pressures and tortures he preserved his faith. Finally, he was killed and his remains were thrown into the sea.
                  The urn with his remains was then sent to a local bishop and became a pilgrimage attraction.
                  He is also represented as a martyr in the Ethiopian Church and his feast is commemorated on 19 Sane.</crm:P78_is_identified_by>
         </crm:E52_Time-span>
